Detailed Description

cvmx_sso_rwq_pop_fptr

SSO_RWQ_POP_FPTR = SSO Pop Free Pointer

This register is used by SW to remove pointers for buffer-reallocation and diagnostics, and should only be used when SSO is idle.

To remove ALL pointers, software must insure that there are modulus 16 pointers in the FPA. To do this, SSO_CFG.RWQ_BYP_DIS must be set, the FPA pointer count read, and enough fake buffers pushed via SSO_RWQ_PSH_FPTR to bring the FPA pointer count up to mod 16.
